<section id="tips">
  <div class="section-wrap">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Science-Backed</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Top Study Techniques</h2>
    <p class="section-desc reveal">Use methods proven by cognitive science to retain more information in less time.</p>
    <div class="tips-grid">
      <div class="tip-card t1 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">🔁</div><h3>Spaced Repetition</h3><p>Review material at increasing intervals. Leverages the forgetting curve to lock knowledge into long-term memory.</p></div>
      <div class="tip-card t2 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">🧪</div><h3>Active Recall</h3><p>Test yourself instead of re-reading. Retrieving information strengthens neural pathways far better than passive review.</p></div>
      <div class="tip-card t3 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">🍅</div><h3>Pomodoro Technique</h3><p>Study in 25-minute focused blocks followed by 5-minute breaks. Prevents burnout and maintains peak concentration.</p></div>
      <div class="tip-card t4 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">🗺️</div><h3>Mind Mapping</h3><p>Connect ideas visually to understand relationships between concepts. Great for complex subjects and holistic learners.</p></div>
      <div class="tip-card t1 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">✍️</div><h3>The Feynman Technique</h3><p>Explain any concept in simple terms as if teaching a child. Gaps in your explanation reveal what you still need to learn.</p></div>
      <div class="tip-card t2 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">😴</div><h3>Sleep & Memory</h3><p>Your brain consolidates memories during sleep. Studying before bedtime and getting 7–8 hours maximizes retention.</p></div>
      <div class="tip-card t3 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">🎯</div><h3>Interleaving Practice</h3><p>Mix different subjects or problem types in one session. Harder but builds more flexible and robust understanding.</p></div>
      <div class="tip-card t4 reveal"><div class="tip-emoji">📝</div><h3>Elaborative Interrogation</h3><p>Ask yourself "why" and "how" about the material. Deep processing leads to far superior memory formation.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

